!iflang [english]

!begin_node Metafile functions

This library contains functions that are indispensable for creating
metafiles. In all, the following routines are available:

!begin_xlist !compressed [x v_meta_extents]
!item [(!bullet) v_meta_extents]
Calculates dimensions of a metafile
!item [(!bullet) v_write_meta]
Stores graphic primitives in a metafile
!item [(!bullet) vm_coords]
Sets new coordinate system for a metafile
!item [(!bullet) vm_filename]
Renames a metafile
!item [(!bullet) vm_pagesize]
Sets physical page size for a metafile
!end_xlist

(!B)Note:(!b) The main purpose of a metafile lies in standardized data
exchange between various (!nolink [GEM]) systems.

See also: (!nl)
Metafile format ~ VDI workstations ~ Style guidelines ~
          VDI fundamentals

